main event: Several objects were tracked on radar and visually observed in flight near Seattle, Washington, on September 6, 1959.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for approximately 5 hours,Multiple objects were reported with erratic flight patterns, The objects usually appeared in pairs and showed a flickering light, Weather conditions were clear but fog moved in shortly after the sighting, Analysis suggested that mirage effects due to temperature inversion may have contributed to the sighting.
sighted object: several round, white and blue objects with flickering lights
